Celebrated cellist Julian Lloyd Webber is to retire from performing as a result of a medical problem which has restricted his ability to play.

The 63-year-old - brother to composer Andrew - said he was 'devastated' to end his career as a musician, which will end with a final performance next week.

Lloyd Webber explained that he has a 'herniated disc' in his neck which has reduced the power in his right arm in which he holds his bow.

