He went on: 'I have no intention of enduring a forced retirement though. I would like to use the knowledge I have gained through my life as a musician and an educator to give back as much as I can to the music profession which has given me so much over the years.

'I have just completed two new recordings which will be released later this year but after May 2 my cello will fall silent.

'I now need time to reflect and to consider this sudden and distressing life-changing situation and there will be no further comment at this time'.

